(449, 1, 21, 61, 1, 1, NULL, 'Samsung Galaxy S7 Edge G935FD - 5.5 inch, Dual SIM - 4G/LTE - Gold', '<div class="title" style="box-sizing: border-box; outline: none; font-size: 14px; line-height: 17px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;">Key Features</div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Display: 5.5 inches Curved edge (~76.1% screen-to-body ratio)</li>\r\n	<li>OS:Android OS, v6.0 (Marshmallow)</li>\r\n	<li>Memory: 32 GB</li>\r\n	<li>RAM: 4 GB&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>single-sim</li>\r\n	<li>Camera:<strong>&nbsp;</strong>(&nbsp;Primary) :12 MP, 5MP front</li>\r\n	<li>Battery: 3600 mAh non-removable</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<h2>Product Specifications</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Display</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Super AMOLED capacitive touchscreen, 16M colors</li>\r\n	<li>Size:5.5 inches (~76.1% screen-to-body ratio)</li>\r\n	<li>Resolution:1440 x 2560 pixels (~534 ppi pixel density)</li>\r\n	<li>Multitouch</li>\r\n	<li>Protection:Corning Gorilla Glass 4</li>\r\n	<li>Always-on display</li>\r\n	<li>TouchWiz UI</li>\r\n	<li>Curved edge screen</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Platform</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>OS:Android OS, v6.0 (Marshmallow)</li>\r\n	<li>Chipset: Qualcomm MSM8996 Snapdragon 820&nbsp;or Exynos 8890 Octa</li>\r\n	<li>CPU: Dual-core 2.15 GHz Kryo &amp; dual-core 1.6 GHz Kryo or&nbsp;Quad-core 2.3 GHz Mongoose + quad-core 1.6 GHz Cortex-A53</li>\r\n	<li>GPU: Adreno 530 or&nbsp;Mali-T880 MP12</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Storage</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Internal Memory:32GB</li>\r\n	<li>RAM:4GB</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Camera</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Primary:12 MP, f/1.7, 26mm, phase detection autofocus, OIS, LED flash</li>\r\n	<li>Features: 1/2.6&quot; sensor size, 1.4 &micro;m pixel size, geo-tagging, simultaneous 4K video and 9MP image recording, touch focus, face/smile detection, Auto HDR, panorama</li>\r\n	<li>Video:2160p@30fps,&nbsp;1080p@60fps,&nbsp;720p@240fps, HDR, dual-video rec.,&nbsp;check quality.</li>\r\n	<li>Secondary:5 MP, f/1.7, 22mm, dual video call, Auto HDR</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Sound</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Alert typesVibration; MP3, WAV ringtones</li>\r\n	<li>Loudspeaker</li>\r\n	<li>3.5mm jack</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Comms</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>WLAN:Wi-Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n/ac, dual-band, Wi-Fi Direct, hotspot</li>\r\n	<li>Bluetoothv:4.2, A2DP, LE, apt-X</li>\r\n	<li>GPS with A-GPS, GLONASS, BDS</li>\r\n	<li>NFC</li>\r\n	<li>USB:microUSB v2.0, USB Host</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Features</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>SensorsFingerprint, accelerometer, gyro, proximity, compass, barometer, heart rate, SpO2</li>\r\n	<li>MessagingSMS(threaded view), MMS, Email, Push Mail, IM</li>\r\n	<li>Fast battery charging: 60% in 30 min (Quick Charge 2.0)</li>\r\n	<li>Wireless charging (Qi/PMA) - market dependent</li>\r\n	<li>ANT+ support</li>\r\n	<li>S-Voice natural language commands and dictation</li>\r\n	<li>OneDrive (115 GB cloud storage)</li>\r\n	<li>Active noise cancellation with dedicated mic</li>\r\n	<li>MP4/DivX/XviD/WMV/H.264 player</li>\r\n	<li>MP3/WAV/WMA/eAAC+/FLAC player</li>\r\n	<li>Photo/video editor</li>\r\n	<li>Document editor</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Battery&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Non-removable Li-Ion 3600 mAh battery</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong><span style="font-size:20px">&nbsp;Samsung Galaxy S7 edge(Single SIm)</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Samsung Galaxy S7 edge is the smartphone you&rsquo;ll want to brag about. It provides a bigger, more stunning screen without compromise.&nbsp;Galaxy S7 edge is lightweight and is encapsulated by an envious, dual curved edge design&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Incredible Design</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The Galaxy S7 edge has an extended edge design that puts more experiences at your fingertips. View information such as scores, stocks, news and more. Quick access to your favorite settings, and useful tools such as compass and ruler. And the Task Edge takes you to frequently accessed commands with just a swipe.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Water and Dust&nbsp;Resistant&nbsp;</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Worry less about daily wear and tear of your phone. Galaxy S7 Edge has an IP68 rating&nbsp;meaning not only protection against dust, it also repels splashes, spills and even dunks. Simply wipe it off and move along.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Expandable Memory</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Running out of memory shouldn&#39;t be a thing. So if 32GB isn&#39;t already enough, you can add an additional 200GB with a microSD card. No clouds, no hard drives.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Enhanced Camera</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The first smartphone with dual-pixel technology has a fast autofocus for less blur and a new advanced sensor for catching details in low light. Capture moments as you actually see them.</p>\r\n', '', '', 'GLN1198', NULL, '', NULL, 'visible', 58299, 54999, 1, 'samsung-galaxy-s7-edge-g935fd-5-5-inch-dual-sim-4g-lte-gold.jpg', 'samsung-galaxy-s7-edge-g935fd-5-5-inch-dual-sim-4g-lte-gold-2.jpg', 'samsung-galaxy-s7-edge-g935fd-5-5-inch-dual-sim-4g-lte-gold-3.jpg', 'samsung-galaxy-s7-edge-g935fd-5-5-inch-dual-sim-4g-lte-gold-4.jpg', 'samsung-galaxy-s7-edge-g935fd-5-5-inch-dual-sim-4g-lte-gold-5.jpg', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'samsung-galaxy-s7-edge-g935fd-5-5-inch-dual-sim-4g-lte-gold', '2017-09-18 16:56:44', '2017-09-18 16:56:44'),
(450, 1, 21, 61, 1, 1, NULL, 'Samsung Galaxy S8, 5.8 -inch, 64GB, 12 MP Camera, Single SIM - black', '<div class="title" style="box-sizing: border-box; line-height: 17px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size:20px">Key Features</span></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Display: 5.8 inches (~83.6% screen-to-body ratio)</li>\r\n	<li>OS: Android OS, v7.0</li>\r\n	<li>Memory: 64 GB</li>\r\n	<li>RAM: 4 GB&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Camera:&nbsp;(&nbsp;Primary) :12 MP, 8MP front</li>\r\n	<li>Battery: Non-removable Li-Ion 3000 mAh battery</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<h2><strong>Product Specifications</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Display</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>TypeSuper AMOLED capacitive touchscreen, 16M colors</li>\r\n	<li>Size5.8 inches (~83.6% screen-to-body ratio)</li>\r\n	<li>Resolution1440 x 2960 pixels (~570 ppi pixel density)</li>\r\n	<li>Multitouch</li>\r\n	<li>ProtectionCorning Gorilla Glass 5</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;Platform</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>OS Android OS, v7.0</li>\r\n	<li>ChipsetQualcomm MSM8998 Snapdragon 835 - US model</li>\r\n	<li>Exynos 8895 Octa - EMEA</li>\r\n	<li>CPUOcta-core (4x2.35 GHz Kryo &amp; 4x1.9 GHz Kryo) - US model</li>\r\n	<li>Octa-core (4x2.3 GHz &amp; 4x1.7 GHz) - EMEA</li>\r\n	<li>GPUAdreno 540 - US model</li>\r\n	<li>Mali-G71 MP20 - EMEA</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Memory</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Card slotmicroSD, up to 256 GB (dedicated slot) - single-SIM model</li>\r\n	<li>MicroSD, up to 256 GB (uses SIM 2 slot) - dual-SIM mode</li>\r\n	<li>Internal64 GB, 4 GB RAM</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Camera</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Primary 12 MP, f/1.7, 26mm, phase detection autofocus, OIS, LED flash</li>\r\n	<li>Features1/2.5&quot; sensor size, 1.4 &micro;m pixel size, geo-tagging, simultaneous 4K video and 9MP image recording, touch focus, face/smile detection, Auto HDR, panorama</li>\r\n	<li>Video2160p@30fps, 1080p@60fps, HDR, dual-video rec.</li>\r\n	<li>Secondary 8 MP, f/1.7, autofocus, 1440p@30fps, dual video call, Auto HDR</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Sound</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Alert typesVibration; MP3, WAV ringtones</li>\r\n	<li>Loud speaker</li>\r\n	<li>3.5mm jack</li>\r\n	<li>32-bit/384kHz audio</li>\r\n	<li>Active noise cancellation with dedicated mic</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Communications</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>WLAN Wi-Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n/ac, dual-band, Wi-Fi Direct, hotspot</li>\r\n	<li>Bluetooth v5.0, A2DP, LE, aptX</li>\r\n	<li>GPS, with A-GPS, GLONASS, BDS, GALILEO</li>\r\n	<li>NFC</li>\r\n	<li>USBv3.1, Type-C 1.0 reversible connector</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Features</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Sensors:Iris scanner, fingerprint (rear-mounted), accelerometer, gyro, proximity, compass, barometer, heart rate, SpO2</li>\r\n	<li>Messaging: SMS(threaded view), MMS, Email, Push Mail, IM</li>\r\n	<li>Browser,HTML5</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Samsung DeX (desktop experience support)</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Fast battery charging</li>\r\n	<li>Qi/PMA wireless charging (market dependent)</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;ANT+ support</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;S-Voice natural language commands and dictation</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;MP4/DivX/XviD/H.265 player</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;MP3/WAV/eAAC+/FLAC player</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Photo/video editor</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Document editor</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Battery</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Non-removable Li-Ion 3000 mAh battery</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><strong><span style="font-size:20px">Samsung Galaxy S8 (5.8 inch)</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Samsung Galaxy S8&#39;s is your perfect companion. It has a perfect balance of form, function, art, science, design and technology. It is our pleasure to introduce an innovation that will change the way you see your smartphone and everything on it. The display forms an unbelievable continuous smooth surface. This new phone has the highest screen to body ratio than ever before,&nbsp;You can barely tell where the screen ends. The result is a beautifully curved and perfectly symmetrical object. The infinity display is more vibrant and richer to enable you to stream shows and movies on your smartphone.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="image" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/SA948EL0NKL2ONAFAMZ/c8b4a16422e55a2d58849fb8fd321e8d.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:510px; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle; width:466px" /><strong>The &quot;Infinity Display&quot;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the Galaxy S8&rsquo;s most interesting features is also one of the most prominent: Samsung&rsquo;s new &ldquo;Infinity Display.&rdquo; That is the fancy name Samsung has given to the curved smartphone that has rounded-off corners. Yes, the shape of the screen is different, but it affects the way the phone will feel in your hand.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="image" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/SA948EL0NKL2ONAFAMZ/6d79df2e62ecb2e13f06909396201a1d.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Slim Bezels</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You might notice all the images of the Galaxy S8 appear to be of the black phone. That&rsquo;s actually just because the front bezel will be black on all models. In the past, Samsung&rsquo;s phones have been the same color on the front and back. So, if you had a silver phone, it was silver on the front&nbsp;<em>and&nbsp;</em>&nbsp;back. The black front panel on this phone is intended to accentuate the look of the Infinity Display and hide the already slim bezels.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="image" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/SA948EL0NKL2ONAFAMZ/d551dd224a9e6fa3af5244d686d72257.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:343px; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle; width:648px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>New and More Durable Battery</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The lithium-ion cells in the Galaxy S8 will retain 95% of their capacity after a year of use. That&rsquo;s great, especially considering the batteries are sealed in. If you&rsquo;re the sort who wants to use a phone for years on end until it dies, you can feel more confident buying a Galaxy S8.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Better Selfie Camera</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Samsung made the biggest changes to the front-facing camera. The selfie camera now captures 8-megapixel photos with a with an f/1.7 lens, and also has autofocus capabilities.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="image" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/SA948EL0NKL2ONAFAMZ/b2672da0906c72476749ae9431e5188e.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:382px; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle; width:680px" /><strong>Bixby</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s 2017, and Samsung has finally introduced its own virtual assistant: Bixby. Samsung is positioning it as a virtual assistant that can help you complete your tasks: you can set reminders, search through photo galleries, and cast your phone screen to your Wi-Fi-connected TV, all by pressing a dedicated Bixby button and talking to it. It&rsquo;s also able to identify physical objects out in the wild...</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="image" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/SA948EL0NKL2ONAFAMZ/cabcddf9d7363f505c5128b6720dcc81.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:524px; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle; width:622px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>DeX</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Using only your phone to power an entire desktop experience has long been the dream of business people. That is where Samsung&rsquo;s DeX comes in. DeX is a plastic bowl like stand which has a a USB-C prong, a couple of ports, and a fan. It supports the Galaxy S8 and effectively gives you a PC-like mobile desktop on display. Some apps are even optimized for the experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/SA948EL0NKL2ONAFAMZ/ad8678f97705cbdf19f5e04eeb48a452.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:260px; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle; width:593px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>3.5MM Headphone Jack</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;The 3.5mm headphone jack is still one of the most welcome features of the Galaxy S8.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="image" src="http://www.techspot.com/images2/news/bigimage/2017/01/2017-01-24-image-19.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:397px; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle; width:600px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Water and Dust&nbsp;Resistant&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Worry less about daily wear and tear of your phone. Galaxy S7 Edge has an IP68 rating&nbsp;meaning not only protection against dust, it also repels splashes, spills and even dunks. Simply wipe it off and move along.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="image" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/SA948EL0NKL2ONAFAMZ/8cae251c1bba5fe493f90684991c86a5.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:314px; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle; width:650px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Expandable Memory</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Running out of memory shouldn&#39;t be a thing. So if 64GB isn&#39;t already enough, you can add an additional 200GB with a microSD card. No clouds, no hard drives.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="Image result for samsung galaxy note 8 expandable memory" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/SA948EL0NKL2ONAFAMZ/e9e097c8dd125341d8424590f77722f5.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle" /></p>\r\n', '', '', 'GLN1199', NULL, '', NULL, 'visible', 80559, 75999, 1, 'galaxy-s8-5-8-inch-64gb-12-mp-camera-single-sim-black.jpg', 'galaxy-s8-5-8-inch-64gb-12-mp-camera-single-sim-black-2.jpg', 'galaxy-s8-5-8-inch-64gb-12-mp-camera-single-sim-black-3.jpg', 'galaxy-s8-5-8-inch-64gb-12-mp-camera-single-sim-black-4.jpg', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'samsung-galaxy-s8-5-8-inch-64gb-12-mp-camera-single-sim-black', '2017-09-18 17:13:35', '2017-09-18 17:13:35'),
(451, 1, 21, 61, 1, 1, NULL, 'Samsung Galaxy J5 Prime (G570 FD), Dual SIM - 4G/LTE - Black', '<div class="title" style="box-sizing: border-box; line-height: 17px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;"><strong><span style="font-size:20px">Key Features</span></strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Display: 5.0&quot; IPS LCD capacitive touchscreen</li>\r\n	<li>OS: Android OS, v6.0.1 (Marshmallow)</li>\r\n	<li>CPU: Quad-core 1.4 GHz Cortex-A53</li>\r\n	<li>Internal: 16 GB, 2 GB RAM</li>\r\n	<li>Camera: 13MP back, 5MP front</li>\r\n	<li>Battery:&nbsp;Non-removable Li-Ion 2400 mAh</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<h2><strong>Product Specifications</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Display</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Type: IPS LCD capacitive touchscreen, 16M colors</li>\r\n	<li>Size: 5.0 inches (~69.4% screen-to-body ratio)</li>\r\n	<li>Resolution: 720 x 1280 pixels (~294 ppi pixel density)</li>\r\n	<li>Multitouch: Yes</li>\r\n	<li>Protection: Corning Gorilla Glass (market dependent)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Platform</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>OS: Android OS, v6.0.1 (Marshmallow)</li>\r\n	<li>CPU: Quad-core 1.4 GHz Cortex-A53</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Memory</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Card slot: microSD, up to 256 GB (dedicated slot)</li>\r\n	<li>Internal: 16 GB, 2 GB RAM</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Camera</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Primary: 13 MP, f/1.9, 28mm, autofocus, LED flash</li>\r\n	<li>FeaturesGeo-tagging, touch focus, face detection, panorama, HDR</li>\r\n	<li>Video:&nbsp;1080p@30fps</li>\r\n	<li>Secondary: 5 MP, f/2.2</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Sound</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Alert types: Vibration; MP3, WAV ringtones</li>\r\n	<li>Loudspeaker</li>\r\n	<li>3.5mm jack</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Comms</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>WLAN: Wi-Fi 802.11 b/g/n, Wi-Fi Direct, hotspot</li>\r\n	<li>Bluetooth: v4.2, A2DP, LE</li>\r\n	<li>GPS: Yes, with A-GPS, GLONASS/ BDS (region dependent)</li>\r\n	<li>USB: microUSB v2.0, USB On-The-Go</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Features</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Sensors: Fingerprint, accelerometer, proximity</li>\r\n	<li>Messaging: SMS(threaded view), MMS, Email, Push Mail, IM</li>\r\n	<li>Browser: HTML5</li>\r\n	<li>Xvid/DivX/MP4/H.265 player</li>\r\n	<li>MP3/WAV/eAAC+/FLAC player</li>\r\n	<li>Photo/video editor</li>\r\n	<li>Document viewer</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Battery</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Non-removable Li-Ion 2400 mAh battery</li>\r\n	<li>Talk timeUp to 16 h (3G)</li>\r\n	<li>Music playUp to 54 h</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:20px"><strong>Samsung Galaxy J5 Prime</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Samsung Galaxy J5 Prime&nbsp;comes with a 5-inch touchscreen display with a resolution of 720 pixels by 1280 pixels. It&nbsp;is powered by 1.4 GHz quad-core with 2GB of RAM. The phone packs 16GB of internal storage that can be expanded up to 256GB via a microSD card. The Galaxy J5 Prime has a 13-megapixel primary camera on the rear and a 5-megapixel front shooter for selfies.&nbsp;<strong>Elegant&nbsp;design</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Boasts a stunning brushed metal finish with zero camera protrusion to ensure an overall ultra slim design. Its enlarged screen features flowing curved edges for optimal viewing and comfortable single-handed use.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Take brighter photos</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Featuring an F1.9 lens that allows for bright images even in low light settings, its 13MP camera ensures that all that you capture is beautifully crisp with vivid detail.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Great selfies</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Its Wide Selfie function together with its front camera lets you fit more people in group shots and capture beautiful scenery as it was meant to be seen. You can even use your palm to take photos with ease.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Powerful</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Enhanced RAM and ROM support allow for smoother UI transitions and greater multitasking abilities. Smart Manager does the thinking for you by checking and optimising handset status, keeping you one step ahead.</p>\r\n', '', '', 'GLN1200', NULL, '', NULL, 'visible', 20563, 19399, 1, 'samsung-samsung-galaxy-j5-prime-g570-fd-dual-sim-4g-lte-black.jpg', 'samsung-samsung-galaxy-j5-prime-g570-fd-dual-sim-4g-lte-black-2.jpg', 'samsung-samsung-galaxy-j5-prime-g570-fd-dual-sim-4g-lte-black-3.jpg', 'samsung-samsung-galaxy-j5-prime-g570-fd-dual-sim-4g-lte-black-4.jpg', 'samsung-samsung-galaxy-j5-prime-g570-fd-dual-sim-4g-lte-black-5.jpg', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'samsung-galaxy-j5-prime-g570-fd-dual-sim-4g-lte-black', '2017-09-18 17:30:40', '2017-09-18 17:30:40'),
(452, 1, 21, 61, 1, 1, NULL, 'Samsung S6 Edge, 16MP Camera, 3GB RAM, Single SIM - Gold', '<div class="title" style="box-sizing: border-box; line-height: 17px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size:20px"><strong>Key Features</strong></span></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Operating System: Android v5.0.2</li>\r\n	<li>Camera Specs: 16 MegaPixels</li>\r\n	<li>Screen: 5.1&quot; 16M Super AMOLED Capacitive Touchscreen</li>\r\n	<li>Memory: 32GB, 3GB RAM</li>\r\n	<li>Battery: 2600mAh Non-Removable</li>\r\n	<li>CPU: ARM Octa Core; 3.6 GHz</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<h2><strong>Product Specifications</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>NETWORK</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>2G: GSM 850 - 900 - 1800 - 1900&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>3G: HSDPA 850 - 900 - 1900 - 2100&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>4G: LTE</li>\r\n	<li>Sim: Nano-Sim</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>DISPLAY</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Size: 5.1 inches&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Type: Super AMOLED capacitive touchscreen,&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Resolution: 1440 x 2560 pixels&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>MEDIA</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Alert types: Vibration; MP3, WAV ringtones&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Loudspeaker: Yes</li>\r\n	<li>3.5mm jack: Yes</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>MEMORY</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Internal: 32 GB</li>\r\n	<li>RAM: 3 GB</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>CONNECTIVITY</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>WLAN: Wi-Fi 802.11 a-b-g-n-ac&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Bluetooth: Bluetooth v4.1</li>\r\n	<li>USB: microUSB v2.0&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>CAMERA</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Primary: 16 MP 2988 x 5312 pixels, Optical Image Stabilization, Autofocus, LED Flash&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Secondary: 5 MP&nbsp;1080p@30fps, Dual Video Call, Auto HDR&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Video:&nbsp;2160p@30fps,&nbsp;1080p@60fps,&nbsp;720p@120fps, HDR&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>BATTERY</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Battery capacity: 2600 mAh&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>FEATURES</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Operating System: Android OS v5.0.2 (Lollipop)&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>CPU Speed: 3.6 GHz&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>CPU Type: Octa-core&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Other Features:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>ANT+ support&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>S-Voice natural language commands and dictation&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Smart stay&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>OneDrive (115 GB cloud storage)&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Active noise cancellation with dedicated mic&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>MP4/DivX/XviD/WMV/H.264 player&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>MP3/WAV/WMA/eAAC+/FLAC player&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Photo/video editor&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Document editor&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p>A brilliant smartphone running on the Android 5.0.2 operating system, the Samsung Galaxy S6 Edge SM-G925 features a sleek design and has been sturdily built to be tough. It sports a 5.1-inch capacitive touchscreen which offers a 1440 x 2560 pixels resolution so every picture will be crystal clear and texts will be bold. The intuitive interface of the Galaxy S6 Edge gives a smooth user experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It comes preinstalled with handy applications and games that will keep you engaged all day. You also have the option of adding more through the application store. With a built-in memory of 128GB, you can adequately save all your pictures, videos, songs and more.<br />\r\n<strong>Dazzling Display</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>One fascinating feature of the Samsung Galaxy S6 is its sleek and bold 5.1 inch amoled display. Enclosed in a dazzling design, it features a sturdy chassis with a curved back that makes it sit comfortably in the hand.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Fast Charging</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Equipped with a non-removable 2600mah battery, the SM-G925 charges fast that you would hardly notice the power lapse on your phone, so you are always on the go and your business at top-speed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Rich interactions with your edge</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Enjoy life on the fast lane with interactions with apps and games on your phone.</p>\r\n', '', '', 'GLN1201', NULL, '', NULL, 'visible', 37099, 34999, 1, 'samsung-samsung-s6-edge-16mp-camera-3gb-ram-single-sim-gold.jpg', 'samsung-samsung-s6-edge-16mp-camera-3gb-ram-single-sim-gold-2.jpg', 'samsung-samsung-s6-edge-16mp-camera-3gb-ram-single-sim-gold-3.jpg', 'samsung-samsung-s6-edge-16mp-camera-3gb-ram-single-sim-gold-4.jpg', 'samsung-samsung-s6-edge-16mp-camera-3gb-ram-single-sim-gold-5.jpg', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'samsung-s6-edge-16mp-camera-3gb-ram-single-sim-gold', '2017-09-18 17:41:39', '2017-09-18 17:41:39'),
