(465, 1, 21, 61, 2, 26, NULL, 'Sony Xperia XA 2GB RAM,16GB,13MP Rear- Single SIM-Black', '<div class="title" style="box-sizing: border-box; line-height: 17px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;"><strong>Key Features</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Processor: Octa-core (4x2.0 GHz Cortex-A53 &amp; 4x1.0 GHz Cortex-A53)</li>\r\n	<li>Camera: 13MP Rear, 8.0MP Front</li>\r\n	<li>Screen Size + Type:<strong>&nbsp;</strong>5.0&quot; IPS LCD capacitive touchscreen s</li>\r\n	<li>OS: Android OS, v6.0.1 (Marshmallow)</li>\r\n	<li>Memory: 16GB ROM, 2GB RAM</li>\r\n	<li>SIM: Nano-SIM</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p><strong><span style="font-family:sst w01 bold,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size:inherit">KEY FEATURES</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-family:sst w01 bold,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size:inherit">SIM CAPABILITY</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Single Sim</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-family:sst w01 bold,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size:inherit">MEMORY AND STORAGE</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Up to 200 GB microSD&trade; card</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-family:sst w01 bold,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size:inherit">WEIGHT</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>137.4g</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-family:sst w01 bold,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size:inherit">DIMENSIONS</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>143.6 x 66.8 x 7.9mm</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-family:sst w01 bold,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size:inherit">DISPLAY</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>12.7cm HD 720p, Mobile BRAVIA engine 2, Super Vivid mode</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-family:sst w01 bold,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size:inherit">CAMERA</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>1/3&#39;&#39; 13MP Exmor RS for mobile sensor, Quick launch, Hybrid Auto-Focus, 5x Clear Image Zoom, Auto-Scene Recognition</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style="font-family:sst w01 bold,helvetica neue,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size:inherit">ON THE INSIDE</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Google Android 6.0 (Marshmallow), MediaTek helio&trade; P10, 64 bit Octa Core processor</p>\r\n', '<p>Upgrade your phone to the latest Sony Xperia XA that comes with the most amazing features. This phone has a 13 MP camera with an all new hybrid autofocus, a 64-bit Octa-Core processor and a 5.0-inch HD display with curved glass. Its memory can be expanded to up to 200 GB with a micro SD card, giving you ample room to store your images, files and apps.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/SO521EL0JL23KNAFAMZ/0d222acd466ce67d5d83cc4b53dac9aa.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:270px; margin:62px auto 30px; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle; width:650px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Full HD Display</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>This Phone boasts of its full HD display with curved glass. Sony has designed this phone for the sole purpose of the best viewing experience and performance. The curved edge display adds to the overall design statement of the Xperia XA.&nbsp; The display stretches to the full width of the phone and uses the Mobile BRAVIA engine 2. It is also provided with a Super-Vivid Mode.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/SO521EL0JL23KNAFAMZ/96f16d59ad37c242ec8aa51e5503df11.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:359px; margin:0px auto 30px; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle; width:638px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Powerful Processor</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The Sony Xperia XA hosts a 64-Bit Octa-Core processor which makes multitasking as easy and lag-free as possible. The 64-Bit Octo-Core processor enhances performance and the 2GB RAM makes the phone suitable for high speed utilizations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/SO521EL0JL23KNAFAMZ/c50ac27a3edfbea93044f05905456d71.jpg" style="border:0px solid; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>13MP Camera</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The camera of the Xperia XA is the main highlight of this phone. It hosts a 13MP primary camera and an 8MP secondary camera. The primary camera features a Exmor RS as a mobile sensor, Quick launch, Hybrid Auto-Focus, 5x Clear Image Zoom, Auto-Scene Recognition and provides you with HDR images. The secondary camera features a Sony Exmor R as a mobile sensor, ensures HDR photos, a wide-angle lens (88 degrees), auto focus. Both cameras have highly responsive sensors that allow for low-light photography.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/SO521EL0JL23KNAFAMZ/c8d3458303dfb084774d64e8609410ae.jpg" style="border:0px solid; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle" /></p>\r\n', '', '', 'JCG1292', NULL, '', NULL, 'visible', 26249, 24999, 1, 'sony-xperia-xa-2gb-ram-16gb-storage-13mp-rear-8-0mp-front-single-sim-gold-color.jpg', 'sony-xperia-xa-2gb-ram-16gb-storage-13mp-rear-8-0mp-front-single-sim-gold-color-2.jpg', 'sony-xperia-xa-2gb-ram-16gb-storage-13mp-rear-8-0mp-front-single-sim-gold-color-3.jpg', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'sony-xperia-xa-2gb-ram-16gb-13mp-rear-single-sim-black', '2017-09-19 16:48:05', '2017-09-19 16:48:05'),
(466, 1, 21, 61, 1, 1, NULL, 'Samsung Galaxy J7 pro, 13MP Camera, 4G LTE, color- black', '<h2><strong>Key Features</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Size:</strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong>5.5 inch&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Storage:</strong>&nbsp;32 GB</li>\r\n	<li><strong>RAM</strong>; 3GB</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Camera</strong>; 13 MP</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Operating System;</strong>&nbsp;Android 7</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Resolution;&nbsp;</strong>1080x1920 Pixels</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<h2><strong>Product Specifications</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>DISPLAY</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Screen size (inches); &nbsp;&nbsp; 5.50</li>\r\n	<li>Touchscreen; &nbsp;&nbsp; Yes</li>\r\n	<li>Resolution; &nbsp;&nbsp; 1080x1920 pixels</li>\r\n	<li>Pixels per inch (PPI); &nbsp;&nbsp; 401</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>HARDWARE</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Processor; &nbsp;&nbsp; 1.6GHz octa-core</li>\r\n	<li>Processor make; &nbsp;&nbsp; Exynos 7870</li>\r\n	<li>RAM ;&nbsp;&nbsp; 3GB</li>\r\n	<li>Internal storage; &nbsp; &nbsp;16GB</li>\r\n	<li>Expandable storage; &nbsp;&nbsp; Yes</li>\r\n	<li>Expandable storage type; &nbsp;&nbsp; microSD</li>\r\n	<li>Expandable storage up to (GB) ;&nbsp;&nbsp; 128</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>CAMERA</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Rear camera&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;13-megapixel</li>\r\n	<li>Flash&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Yes</li>\r\n	<li>Front camera&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;13-megapixel</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>SOFTWARE</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Operating System&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Android 7.0</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>CONNECTIVITY</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Wi-Fi; &nbsp;&nbsp; Yes</li>\r\n	<li>Wi-Fi standards supported ;&nbsp; 802.11 b/g/n</li>\r\n	<li>GPS; &nbsp;&nbsp; Yes</li>\r\n	<li>Bluetooth; &nbsp;&nbsp; Yes, v 4.10</li>\r\n	<li>NFC ;&nbsp;&nbsp; Yes</li>\r\n	<li>Infrared; &nbsp;&nbsp; No</li>\r\n	<li>USB OTG; &nbsp;&nbsp; Yes</li>\r\n	<li>Headphones; &nbsp;&nbsp; 3.5mm</li>\r\n	<li>FM ;&nbsp;&nbsp; No</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Number of SIMs&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;2<br />\r\nSIM 1&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>GSM/CDM&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; GSM</li>\r\n	<li>3G&nbsp;&nbsp; No</li>\r\n	<li>4G/ LT&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Yes</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nSIM 2&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\n3&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; No<br />\r\n4G/ LT&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Yes<br />\r\n<br />\r\nSENSORS</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Compass/ Magnetometer; &nbsp;&nbsp; Yes</li>\r\n	<li>Proximity sensor; &nbsp;&nbsp; Ye</li>\r\n	<li>Accelerometer; &nbsp;&nbsp; Yes</li>\r\n	<li>Ambient light sensor; &nbsp;&nbsp; Yes</li>\r\n	<li>Gyroscope; &nbsp;&nbsp; Yes</li>\r\n	<li>Barometer; &nbsp;&nbsp; No</li>\r\n	<li>Temperature sensor; &nbsp;&nbsp; No</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>BATTERY</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Non-removable Li-Ion&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>3600 mAh battery</li>\r\n	<li>Talk time Up to 24 h (3G)</li>\r\n	<li>Music playUp to 91 h</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<h1 style="text-align:center"><strong>Samsung Galaxy J7 Pro</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Samsung Galaxy J7 Pro smartphone was launched in June 2017. The phone comes with a 5.50-inch touchscreen display with a resolution of 1080 pixels by 1920 pixels at a PPI of 401 pixels per inch. Samsung Galaxy J7 Pro price in India starts from Rs. 20,900. The Samsung Galaxy J7 Pro is powered by 1.6GHz octa-core Exynos 7870 processor and it comes with 3GB of RAM. The phone packs 16GB of internal storage that can be expanded up to 128GB via a microSD card. As far as the cameras are concerned, the Samsung Galaxy J7 Pro packs a 13-megapixel primary camera on the rear and a 13-megapixel front shooter for selfies.The Samsung Galaxy J7 Pro runs Android 7.0 and is powered by a 3600mAh non removable battery. It measures 152.40 x 74.70 x 7.90 (height x width x thickness) .The Samsung Galaxy J7 Pro is a dual SIM (GSM) . Connectivity options include Wi-Fi, GPS, Bluetooth, NFC, USB OTG and 4G (with support for Band 40 used by some LTE networks in India). Sensors on the phone include Compass Magnetometer, Proximity sensor, Accelerometer, Ambient light sensor and Gyroscope.&nbsp;<br />\r\n<img alt="Image result for samsung logo" src="https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQlTQqiWEAwjxxbMzittwRLKa4iwdN9vbCKwVYpudm9lf4xLP0A" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Elegant by nature</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>When style complements functionality. Designed with the strictest attention to detail, the new Samsung Galaxy J7 Pro features a stunning uniform metal finish with zero camera protrusion for superior grip and 2.5D Glass shielding its 5.5&rdquo; Full HD Super AMOLED display for added durability.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="Elegant by nature" src="http://images.samsung.com/is/image/samsung/my-feature-elegant-by-nature-69713695?$FB_TYPE_A_JPG$" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:450px; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle; width:800px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Share life as you see it</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Its rear 13 MP F1.7 camera captures clear photos with enhanced detail in low light while its intuitive interface enables one-handed functionality thanks to its moving shutter button so you can still take the shot while adjusting your pose or framing the scene.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="Share life as you see it" src="http://images.samsung.com/is/image/samsung/my-feature-share-life-as-you-see-it-69713689?$FB_TYPE_A_JPG$" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:450px; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle; width:800px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Look great in every frame</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Samsung Galaxy J7 Pro lets you take bright and vivid selfies every time with more accurate detail even in low light thanks to its front LED and selfie flashes. You can also control the shutter by simple hand gesture.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="Look great in every frame" src="http://images.samsung.com/is/image/samsung/my-feature-look-great-in-every-frame-69713677?$FB_TYPE_A_JPG$" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:450px; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle; width:800px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Personalized gatekeeper</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The Samsung Galaxy J7 Pro is engineered with a touch-based fingerprint sensor authentication to ensure your data is seen by you alone. You can also use this method for mobile payments, online sign in and verifying online accounts to ensure maximum protection.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="Personalized gatekeeper" src="http://images.samsung.com/is/image/samsung/my-feature-personalized-gatekeeper-69713691?$FB_TYPE_A_JPG$" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:450px; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle; width:800px" /></p>\r\n', '', '', 'GLN1206', NULL, '', NULL, 'visible', 31799, 29999, 1, 'samsung-samsung-galaxy-j7-pro-13mp-camera-4g-lte-color-gold.jpg', 'samsung-samsung-galaxy-j7-pro-13mp-camera-4g-lte-color-gold-2.jpg', 'samsung-samsung-galaxy-j7-pro-13mp-camera-4g-lte-color-gold-3.jpg', 'samsung-samsung-galaxy-j7-pro-13mp-camera-4g-lte-color-gold-4.jpg', 'samsung-samsung-galaxy-j7-pro-13mp-camera-4g-lte-color-gold-5.jpg', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'samsung-galaxy-j7-pro-13mp-camera-4g-lte-color-black', '2017-09-19 16:56:54', '2017-09-19 16:56:54'),
(467, 1, 21, 61, 2, 1, NULL, 'Samsung Galaxy J5 Prime,2GB RAM,13MP Camera,16GB,Dual', '<h2><strong>Key Features</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Display: 5.0&quot; IPS LCD capacitive touchscreen</li>\r\n	<li>OS: Android OS, v6.0.1 (Marshmallow)</li>\r\n	<li>CPU: Quad-core 1.4 GHz Cortex-A53</li>\r\n	<li>Internal: 16 GB, 2 GB RAM</li>\r\n	<li>Camera: 13MP back, 5MP front</li>\r\n	<li>Battery:&nbsp;Non-removable Li-Ion 2400 mAh</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<h2><strong>Product Specifications</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Display</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Type: IPS LCD capacitive touchscreen, 16M colors</li>\r\n	<li>Size: 5.0 inches (~69.4% screen-to-body ratio)</li>\r\n	<li>Resolution: 720 x 1280 pixels (~294 ppi pixel density)</li>\r\n	<li>Multitouch: Yes</li>\r\n	<li>Protection: Corning Gorilla Glass (market dependent)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Platform</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>OS: Android OS, v6.0.1 (Marshmallow)</li>\r\n	<li>CPU: Quad-core 1.4 GHz Cortex-A53</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Memory</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Card slot: microSD, up to 256 GB (dedicated slot)</li>\r\n	<li>Internal: 16 GB, 2 GB RAM</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Camera</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Primary: 13 MP, f/1.9, 28mm, autofocus, LED flash</li>\r\n	<li>FeaturesGeo-tagging, touch focus, face detection, panorama, HDR</li>\r\n	<li>Video:&nbsp;1080p@30fps</li>\r\n	<li>Secondary: 5 MP, f/2.2</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Sound</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Alert types: Vibration; MP3, WAV ringtones</li>\r\n	<li>Loudspeaker</li>\r\n	<li>3.5mm jack</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Comms</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>WLAN: Wi-Fi 802.11 b/g/n, Wi-Fi Direct, hotspot</li>\r\n	<li>Bluetooth: v4.2, A2DP, LE</li>\r\n	<li>GPS: Yes, with A-GPS, GLONASS/ BDS (region dependent)</li>\r\n	<li>USB: microUSB v2.0, USB On-The-Go</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Features</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Sensors: Fingerprint, accelerometer, proximity</li>\r\n	<li>Messaging: SMS(threaded view), MMS, Email, Push Mail, IM</li>\r\n	<li>Browser: HTML5</li>\r\n	<li>Xvid/DivX/MP4/H.265 player</li>\r\n	<li>MP3/WAV/eAAC+/FLAC player</li>\r\n	<li>Photo/video editor</li>\r\n	<li>Document viewer</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Battery</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Non-removable Li-Ion 2400 mAh battery</li>\r\n	<li>Talk timeUp to 16 h (3G)</li>\r\n	<li>Music playUp to 54 h</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<h1 style="text-align:center"><strong>Samsung Galaxy J5 Prime</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Samsung Galaxy J5 Prime&nbsp;comes with a 5-inch touchscreen display with a resolution of 720 pixels by 1280 pixels. It&nbsp;is powered by 1.4 GHz quad-core with 2GB of RAM. The phone packs 16GB of internal storage that can be expanded up to 256GB via a microSD card. The Galaxy J5 Prime has a 13-megapixel primary camera on the rear and a 5-megapixel front shooter for selfies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="Image result for samsung logo" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/SA948EL007IDCNAFAMZ/3c73d3d5cde02340209afd5470b28ae6.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Elegant&nbsp;design</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Boasts a stunning brushed metal finish with zero camera protrusion to ensure an overall ultra slim design. Its enlarged screen features flowing curved edges for optimal viewing and comfortable single handed use.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="image" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/SA948EL007IDCNAFAMZ/827ddca1f34a28eb52f8b150601a1d06.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:428px; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle; width:800px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Take brighter photos</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Featuring an F1.9 lens that allows for bright images even in low light settings, its 13MP camera ensures that all that you capture is beautifully crisp with vivid detail.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="image" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/SA948EL007IDCNAFAMZ/76b783b704c8a360fc1c3f689187344a.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:428px; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle; width:800px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Great selfies</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Its Wide Selfie function together with its front camera lets you fit more people in group shots and capture beautiful scenery as it was meant to be seen. You can even use your palm to take photos with ease.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="image" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/SA948EL007IDCNAFAMZ/07ea3facef6362093527c139195fe816.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:428px; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle; width:800px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Powerful</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Enhanced RAM and ROM support allows for smoother UI transitions and greater multitasking abilities. Smart Manager does the thinking for you by checking and optimising handset status, keeping you one step ahead.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="image" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/SA948EL007IDCNAFAMZ/d56016d83e51781d640d942dfe30dcf2.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:428px; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle; width:800px" /></p>\r\n', '', '', 'GLN1207', NULL, '', NULL, 'visible', 20684, 19699, 1, 'samsung-galaxy-j5-prime-2gb-ram-13mp-camera-16gb-dual-sim-color-gold.jpg', 'samsung-galaxy-j5-prime-2gb-ram-13mp-camera-16gb-dual-sim-color-gold-2.jpg', 'samsung-galaxy-j5-prime-2gb-ram-13mp-camera-16gb-dual-sim-color-gold-3.jpg', 'samsung-galaxy-j5-prime-2gb-ram-13mp-camera-16gb-dual-sim-color-gold-4.jpg', 'samsung-galaxy-j5-prime-2gb-ram-13mp-camera-16gb-dual-sim-color-gold-5.jpg', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'samsung-galaxy-j5-prime-2gb-ram-13mp-camera-16gb-dual', '2017-09-19 17:10:06', '2017-09-19 17:10:06'),
(468, 1, 21, 61, 2, 26, NULL, 'Sony Xperia XA1(23MP,32GB,3GB RAM,5Inch,Dual SIM)-Black', '<ul style="margin-left:18px; margin-right:0px">\r\n	<li><span style="color:rgb(17, 17, 17)">5&rdquo; borderless display with scratch-resistant Corning Gorilla Glass and curved glass edges</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="color:rgb(17, 17, 17)">1/2.3&rdquo; 23 MP main camera with updated Sony Exmor RS image sensor, Hybrid Autofocus, 0.6 second quick capture, and a camera shutter button with Quick Launch. 24mm wide-angle F2.0 lens and ISO6400 support. Sony SteadyShot video stabilization</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="color:rgb(17, 17, 17)">1/4&quot; 8 MP front-facing camera equipped with Sony Exmor R sensor and ISO 3203</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="color:rgb(17, 17, 17)">MediaTek helio P20 64-bit Octa-core processor with 4G LTE Cat 6 support. 3GB RAM and 32GB internal memory storage3 with microSD expansion slot2 supporting up to 256GB memory</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="color:rgb(17, 17, 17)">Unlocked and compatible with GSM/LTE carriers utilizing GSM network such as AT&amp;T, T-Mobile, Straight Talk, MetroPCS, Cricket Wireless, Simple Mobile, Bright spot, and others</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p><strong>Technical Specifications&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Memory and Storage</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>3GB RAM</li>\r\n	<li>32GB eMMC internal memory1</li>\r\n	<li>microSDXC support (up to 256GB)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>SIM capability</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Single SIM</li>\r\n	<li>Dual SIM</li>\r\n	<li>Nano SIM</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Operating System</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Google Android&trade; N</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Processor (CPU)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>MediaTek Helio P20 Octa Core 64bit (Quad core 2.3GHz + Quad core 1.6GHz)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Battery</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>2300mAh</li>\r\n	<li>Qnovo Adaptive Charging</li>\r\n	<li>STAMINA Mode</li>\r\n	<li>Quick Charging (MediaTek PumpExpress 2.0)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Durability</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Corning&reg; Gorilla&reg; Glass</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>Display and Design</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>5&quot; HD 720p</li>\r\n	<li>Image Enhance Technology</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Main Camera</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>23MP</li>\r\n	<li>1/2.3&rdquo; Exmor RS&trade; for mobile image sensor</li>\r\n	<li>Hybrid Autofocus</li>\r\n	<li>Quick Launch &amp; Capture</li>\r\n	<li>Low-light photo: ISO6400</li>\r\n	<li>24mm wide-angle f2.0 lens</li>\r\n	<li>5x Clear Image Zoom</li>\r\n	<li>SteadyShot&trade;</li>\r\n	<li>Low-light video: ISO 3200</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Front Camera</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>8MP</li>\r\n	<li>1/4&quot; Exmor R for mobile&trade; for mobile image sensor</li>\r\n	<li>Low-light photo: up to ISO 3200</li>\r\n	<li>23mm wide-angle lens f2.0</li>\r\n	<li>SteadyShot&trade;</li>\r\n	<li>Low-light video: ISO 3200</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Networks</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>GSM GPRS/EDGE (2G)</li>\r\n	<li>UMTS HSPA+ (3G)</li>\r\n	<li>LTE (4G) Cat4/Cat62</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Connectivity</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>A-GNSS (GPS + GLONASS)2</li>\r\n	<li>WiFi Miracast</li>\r\n	<li>Bluetooth&reg; 4.2 wireless technology</li>\r\n	<li>Google Cast</li>\r\n	<li>NFC</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sound</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>xLOUD</li>\r\n	<li>ClearAudio+</li>\r\n	<li>Stereo Recording</li>\r\n	<li>Bluetooth&reg; 4.2 wireless technology, aptX / A2DP</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul style="margin-left:18px; margin-right:0px">\r\n	<li>Upgrade your phone to the latest Sony Xperia XA that comes with the most amazing features. This phone has a 13 MP camera with an all new hybrid autofocus, a 64-bit Octa-Core processor and a 5.0-inch HD display with curved glass. Its memory can be expanded to up to 200 GB with a micro SD card, giving you ample room to store your images, files and apps.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/SO521EL0JL23KNAFAMZ/0d222acd466ce67d5d83cc4b53dac9aa.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:270px; margin:62px auto 30px; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle; width:650px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Full HD Display</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>This Phone boasts of its full HD display with curved glass. Sony has designed this phone for the sole purpose of the best viewing experience and performance. The curved edge display adds to the overall design statement of the Xperia XA.&nbsp; The display stretches to the full width of the phone and uses the Mobile BRAVIA engine 2. It is also provided with a Super-Vivid Mode.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/SO521EL0JL23KNAFAMZ/96f16d59ad37c242ec8aa51e5503df11.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:359px; margin:0px auto 30px; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle; width:638px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Powerful Processor</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The Sony Xperia XA hosts a 64-Bit Octa-Core processor which makes multitasking as easy and lag-free as possible. The 64-Bit Octo-Core processor enhances performance and the 2GB RAM makes the phone suitable for high speed utilizations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/SO521EL0JL23KNAFAMZ/c50ac27a3edfbea93044f05905456d71.jpg" style="border:0px solid; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>13MP Camera</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The camera of the Xperia XA is the main highlight of this phone. It hosts a 13MP primary camera and an 8MP secondary camera. The primary camera features a Exmor RS as a mobile sensor, Quick launch, Hybrid Auto-Focus, 5x Clear Image Zoom, Auto-Scene Recognition and provides you with HDR images. The secondary camera features a Sony Exmor R as a mobile sensor, ensures HDR photos, a wide-angle lens (88 degrees), auto focus. Both cameras have highly responsive sensors that allow for low-light photography.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/SO521EL0JL23KNAFAMZ/c8d3458303dfb084774d64e8609410ae.jpg" style="border:0px solid; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle" /></p>\r\n', '', '', 'JCG1293', NULL, '', NULL, 'visible', 26187, 24940, 1, 'sony-xperia-xa1-23mp-32gb-3gb-ram-5inch-dual-sim-black.jpg', 'sony-xperia-xa1-23mp-32gb-3gb-ram-5inch-dual-sim-black-2.jpg', 'sony-xperia-xa1-23mp-32gb-3gb-ram-5inch-dual-sim-black-3.jpg', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'sony-xperia-xa1-23mp-32gb-3gb-ram-5inch-dual-sim-black', '2017-09-19 17:13:32', '2017-09-19 17:13:32'),
