(Nano + Nano)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="oppo f3 plus device" class="alignnone size-full td-animation-stack-type1-1 wp-image-2362" src="https://kenyaprice.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/oppo-f3-plus-device.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:inline-block; height:auto; margin:0px 5px; max-width:100%; width:640px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><u>ANNOUNCED</u></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Status: Available</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Global Release Date: 2017, March</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Kenyan Release Date: 2017</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><u>BODY</u></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Dimensions: 163.63 x 80.8 x 7.35 mm</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Weight: 185 g</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><u>DISPLAY</u></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Screen size: 6.0 inches</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Form Factor: Touch</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Screen resolution: 1080 x 1920 pixels</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Touchscreen: Capacitive Touchscreen</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Technology (Display Type): IPS LCD</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="oppo f3 plus display specifications" class="alignnone size-full td-animation-stack-type1-1 wp-image-2363" src="https://kenyaprice.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/oppo-f3-plus-displaay.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:inline-block; height:auto; margin:0px 5px; max-width:100%; width:640px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u>PROCESSOR</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>CPU: Octa-core (4&times;1.95 GHz Cortex-A72 &amp; 4&times;1.44 GHz Cortex-A53)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>GPU: Adreno 510</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Chipset: Qualcomm MSM8976 Pro Snapdragon 653</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><u>STORAGE</u></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Internal Storage: 64 GB Storage</p>\r\n\r\n<p>RAM: 4 GB RAM</p>\r\n\r\n<p>External Storage: up to 256 GB</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Card Slot: microSD Card</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Phonebook: Unlimited</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Messaging: SMS, MMS, Email, Push Mail</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Call Records: Unlimited</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="oppo f3 plus fingerprint scanner" class="alignnone size-full td-animation-stack-type1-1 wp-image-2364" src="https://kenyaprice.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/oppo-f3-plus.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:inline-block; height:auto; margin:0px 5px; max-width:100%; width:640px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><u>CAMERA</u></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Primary camera: 16 MP Camera</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Front Camera: 16 MP + 8 MP Dual Camera</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Video Recording:&nbsp;2160p@30fps,&nbsp;1080p@30fps</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Camera Features: Geo Tagging, HDR</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><u>MULTIMEDIA</u></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Audio Player: MP3, WAV, eAAC+, FLAC</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Video Player: MP4, DivX, XviD, WMV, H.264, H.263</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Games: Yes</p>\r\n\r\n<p>FM Radio: No</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Speakers: Yes</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Audio Jack: 3.5mm Audio Jack</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="oppo-f3-plus-Jumia-Price" class="alignnone size-full td-animation-stack-type1-1 wp-image-2365" src="https://kenyaprice.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/oppo-f3-plus-Jumia-Price.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:inline-block; height:auto; margin:0px 5px; max-width:100%; width:640px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><u>OPPO F3 PLUS BATTERY</u></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Type: Non-removable Li-Ion 4000 mAh battery</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Stand by: NA</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Talk time: NA</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><u>CONNECTIVITY</u></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>GPRS: Yes</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Edge: Yes</p>\r\n\r\n<p>WLAN: Wi-Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n/ac, dual-band, WiFi Direct, hotspot</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Bluetooth: v4.1, A2DP, LE</p>\r\n\r\n<p>USB: microUSB v2.0</p>\r\n\r\n<p>GPS Facility: with A-GPS</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Browser: HTML5</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3G Speed: HSPA 42.2/5.76 Mbps, LTE-A (2CA) Cat6 300/50 Mbps</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="oppo-f3-plus-Kenya" class="alignnone size-full td-animation-stack-type1-1 wp-image-2366" src="https://kenyaprice.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/oppo-f3-plus-Kenya.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:inline-block; height:auto; margin:0px 5px; max-width:100%; width:500px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u>NETWORK SUPPORT</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>3G: HSDPA 850 / 900 / 1900 / 2100 MHz</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2G: GSM 850 / 900 / 1800 / 1900 MHz</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4G: LTE</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u>OTHER FEATURES</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sensors Fingerprint Sensor</p>\r\n', '<p>The highlight of the device is Dual Front camera set up. One is a 16MP&nbsp;camera that comes with&nbsp;1/3 inch sensor and&nbsp;aperture f/2.0. The other is 8MP that supports120-degree wide-angle lens with a 6P lens.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Oppo F3 Plus Smartphone was launched in March 2017, comes with a 6-inch Full HD IPS LCD Capacitive touchscreen with a resolution of 1080 x 1920 pixels at a pixel density of 367 pixels per inch. The screen is also protected by a Corning Gorilla Glass Scratch Resistant display.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The phone is 7.35-mm thin , and tips the scale at 185 grams. The phone is powered by a 1.95 GHz Octa core Qualcomm Snapdragon 653 processor and it comes with 4 GB of RAM. What this means is the processor has Octa cores in the CPU and 4 GB of RAM ensures the phone runs smoothly with multiple applications open simultaneously. The Oppo F3 Plus also packs in a graphics processor, and 64 GB of internal storage which can be expanded to 256 GB via a microSD card.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Oppo F3 Plus runs Android 6.0 OS and is powered by a 4000 mAh battery. Its a Dual SIM Smartphone, and connectivity options on the Oppo F3 Plus include , GPS, HotSpot,Wifi,Bluetooth.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The main camera on the Oppo F3 Plus is a 16 MP shooter with Auto Focus, Face Detection, HDR, Panorama Mode, Touch Focus, Digital Zoom, Video Recording. The smartphone also has a Front Facing Camera capable of shooting 16 &amp; 8 MP selfies.</p>\r\n', '', '', 'GLN1228', NULL, '', NULL, 'visible', 38159, 35999, 1, 'oppo-f3-plus.jpg', 'oppo-f3-plus-2.jpg', 'oppo-f3-plus-3.jpg', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'oppo-f3-plus', '2017-09-21 17:59:01', '2017-09-21 17:59:01'),
