(504, 1, 21, 61, 2, 27, NULL, 'Oppo F1s(13MP CAMERA,4GB RAM, 64GB) GOLD', '<p><strong>Key Features</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>13MP primary camera 16MP front facing camera</li>\r\n	<li>13.97 centimeters (5.5-inch) TFT IPS capacitive touchscreen with 1280 x 720 pixels resolution and 267 ppi pixel density</li>\r\n	<li>Android v5.1 operating system with 1.5GHz 64-bit octa core processor</li>\r\n	<li>4GB RAM, 64GB internal memory expandable up to 128GB</li>\r\n	<li>Dual SIM (nano+nano) dual-standby (4G+4G)</li>\r\n	<li>3075mAH lithium-ion battery providing talk-time of 28.5 hours and standby time of 281 hours</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p><br />\r\n<strong>CPU</strong>: 4x 1.5 GHz ARM Cortex-A53, 4x 1.0 GHz ARM Cortex-A53,&nbsp;<strong>Cores</strong>: 8<br />\r\n<strong>GPU</strong>: ARM Mali-T860 MP2, 520 MHz,&nbsp;<strong>Cores</strong>: 2<br />\r\n<strong>RAM</strong>: 4 GB, 667 MHz<br />\r\n<strong>Storage</strong>: 64 GB<br />\r\n<strong>Memory cards</strong>: microSD, microSDHC, microSDXC<br />\r\n<strong>Display</strong>: 5.5 in, IPS, 720 x 1280 pixels, 24 bit<br />\r\n<strong>Battery</strong>: 3075 mAh, Li-Polymer<br />\r\n<strong>OS</strong>: ColorOS 3.0 (Android 5.1.1 Lollipop)<br />\r\n<strong>Camera</strong>: 4160 x 3120 pixels, 1920 x 1080 pixels, 30 fps<br />\r\n<strong>SIM card</strong>: Nano-SIM<br />\r\n<strong>Wi-Fi</strong>:&nbsp; 5GHz, Dual band, Wi-Fi Hotspot<br />\r\n<strong>USB</strong>: 2.0, Micro USB<br />\r\n<strong>Bluetooth</strong>: 4.0<br />\r\n<strong>Positioning</strong>: GPS, A-GPS</p>\r\n', '<p>Oppo F1s is a well-designed smartphones with many amazing features. A good selfie camera is not the only thing that you are going to get when you buy this phone. The F1s is beautifully designed phone with curved edges that makes it easy to hold it in one hand. It has slim bezels that further help to enhance its look.&nbsp; The screen is protected by Gorilla Glass 4.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Oppo F1s is powered by MediaTek MT6750 octacore processor clocking at 1.5GHz.&nbsp; It comes with 3GB of RAM and 32GB internal storage.&nbsp; Other specifications of the Oppo F1s include Bluetooth v4.0, dual-band Wi-Fi b/g/n, USB OTG, FM radio and GPS. Unfortunately, there is no NFC. This phones runs on Android v5.1 Lollipop out-of-the-box. You can upgrade to Android v6.0 Marshmallow.&nbsp; The Android OS is customized by <a href="https://onlineshoppingkenya.com/oppo-phones-price-list/">Oppo&rsquo;s</a> Color OS 3.0.&nbsp; This phone can handle most of the things that an average user can throw at it. You should expect to play games, including 3D games without any glaring issues.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The key reason why moshttps://wamu.co.ke/products/createt people will pick the Oppo F1s is its cameras. The front camera is the highlight of the phone.&nbsp; The front camera has a 16MP sensor and an f/2.0 aperture.&nbsp; This camera gives pretty detailed photos even in low light conditions.&nbsp; The camera comes with beautify 4.0- this allows one to get rid of blemishes. The front camera can also record 1080p videos.&nbsp; The 13MP rear camera is also amazing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Oppo F1s comes with a 3070mAh battery. Under regular use, this phone will easily take you through the day.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="Oppo F1s price" class="aligncenter size-full td-animation-stack-type0-2 wp-image-7379" src="https://onlineshoppingkenya.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/Oppo-F1s-price.png" style="height:389px; width:336px" /></p>\r\n', '', '', 'JCG1309', NULL, '', NULL, 'visible', 29400, 28000, 1, 'oppo-f1s-13mp-camera-4gb-ram-64gb-gold.jpg', 'oppo-f1s-13mp-camera-4gb-ram-64gb-gold-2.jpg', 'oppo-f1s-13mp-camera-4gb-ram-64gb-gold-3.jpg', 'oppo-f1s-13mp-camera-4gb-ram-64gb-gold-4.jpg', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'oppo-f1s-13mp-camera-4gb-ram-64gb-gold', '2017-09-21 19:37:30', '2017-09-21 19:37:30'),
(505, 1, 21, 61, 2, 27, NULL, 'OPPO F3 (13MP Camera, 64GB, 4GB RAM, Dual SIM 5.5 Inch) Gold', '<div class="title"><strong>Key Features</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>5.5&quot; FullHD IPS screen</li>\r\n	<li>Dual SIM 4G</li>\r\n	<li>Triple Slots (Dual SIM cards + microSDcard)</li>\r\n	<li>Android 6.0</li>\r\n	<li>64GB ROM + 4GB RAM</li>\r\n	<li>3200mAh Non-removable Battery</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p><strong>CPU</strong>: 4x 1.5 GHz ARM Cortex-A53, 4x 1.0 GHz ARM Cortex-A53,&nbsp;<strong>Cores</strong>: 8<br />\r\n<strong>GPU</strong>: ARM Mali-T860 MP2, 650 MHz,&nbsp;<strong>Cores</strong>: 2<br />\r\n<strong>RAM</strong>: 4 GB, 833 MHz<br />\r\n<strong>Storage</strong>: 64 GB<br />\r\n<strong>Memory cards</strong>: microSD, microSDHC, microSDXC<br />\r\n<strong>Display</strong>: 5.5 in, IPS, 1080 x 1920 pixels, 24 bit<br />\r\n<strong>Battery</strong>: 3200 mAh, Li-Polymer<br />\r\n<strong>OS</strong>: ColorOS 3.0 (Android 6.0.1 Marshmallow)<br />\r\n<strong>Camera</strong>: 4160 x 3120 pixels, 1920 x 1080 pixels, 30 fps<br />\r\n<strong>SIM card</strong>: Nano-SIM<br />\r\n<strong>Wi-Fi</strong>: a, b, g, n, n 5GHz, Dual band, Wi-Fi Hotspot, Wi-Fi Display<br />\r\n<strong>USB</strong>: 2.0, Micro USB<br />\r\n<strong>Bluetooth</strong>: 4.1<br />\r\n<strong>Positioning</strong>: GPS, A-GPS, GLONASS&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '<h3><strong>OPPO F3 SPECIFICATIONS</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="OPPO F3 Smartphone full sepecifications" class="alignnone size-full td-animation-stack-type1-2 wp-image-2223" src="https://kenyaprice.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/mobile_oppo-f3-36322.jpg" style="height:375px; width:600px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><u>GENERAL</u></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Operating System: Android OS, v6.0 (Marshmallow)</li>\r\n	<li>Device type: Smartphone</li>\r\n	<li>Sim: Dual Sim (Nano + Nano)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>As mentioned earlier, the device supports <strong>dual sim,</strong> so you can take advantage of cheaper calling rates and data.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With the v6.0 of android, you get performance improvements and better battery management compared to the predecessor.<img alt="OPPO F3 Price in Kenya" class="alignnone size-full td-animation-stack-type1-2 wp-image-2218" src="https://kenyaprice.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/oppo-f3_149396281110.jpg" style="height:424px; width:640px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><u>ANNOUNCED</u></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Status: Available</li>\r\n	<li>Global Release Date: 2017, May</li>\r\n	<li>Kenyan Release Date: 2017, May 15</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><u>BODY</u></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Dimensions: 153.3 x 75.2 x 7.3 mm</li>\r\n	<li>Weight: 153 g</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>This is a premium phone and thus has a very thin body of only 7.3mm. this is thinner than all the phones in Kenya at that price range.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Also it weighs 153 grams and therefore relatively light.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="oppo f3 Jumia Kenya price" class="alignnone size-full td-animation-stack-type1-2 wp-image-2220" src="https://kenyaprice.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/oppo-f3_149396281150.jpg" style="height:375px; width:600px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><u>OPPO F3 DISPLAY</u></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Screen size: 5.5 inches</li>\r\n	<li>Form Factor: Touch</li>\r\n	<li>Screen resolution: 1080 x 1920 pixels</li>\r\n	<li>Touchscreen: Capacitive Touchscreen</li>\r\n	<li>Technology (Display Type): IPS LCD</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The OPPO F3 has one of the best display in this category of phones. You get a 5.5 inch display coipled with a resolution of 1080 x 1920 pixels. The IPS LCD display is sharp and clear because of the high resolution.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="Display Quality of OPPO F3 Mobile Phone" class="alignnone size-full td-animation-stack-type1-2 wp-image-2224" src="https://kenyaprice.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/mobile_oppo-f3-3.jpg" style="height:400px; width:640px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><u>OPPO F3 PROCESSOR</u></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>CPU: Octa Core 1.5 GHz</li>\r\n	<li>GPU: Adreno</li>\r\n	<li>Chipset Mediatek MT6750T</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The performance of this cell phone is also noteworthy. You get an Octa Core processor which is clocked at 1.5GHz. Therefore, app launches will be fast and gameplay smooth. In addition, there is an Adreno GPU which leads to good performance from graphic intensive games and applications.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="oppo f3 finger print scanner" class="alignnone size-full td-animation-stack-type1-2 wp-image-2226" src="https://kenyaprice.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/oppo-f3_149396281130.jpg" style="height:375px; width:600px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><u>STORAGE</u></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Internal Storage: 64 GB Storage</li>\r\n	<li>RAM: 4 GB RAM</li>\r\n	<li>External Storage: up to 128 GB</li>\r\n	<li>Card Slot: microSD Card</li>\r\n	<li>Phonebook: Unlimited</li>\r\n	<li>Messaging: SMS, MMS, Email, Push Mail</li>\r\n	<li>Call Records: Unlimited</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="Battery Specifications &amp; Features of OPPO F3" class="alignnone size-full td-animation-stack-type1-2 wp-image-2229" src="https://kenyaprice.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/oppo-f3_1493962811100.jpg" style="height:400px; width:640px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The OPPO F3 comes with a whooping 64GB of storage. This is one of the strongest points in this phone. You can store thousands of music, many files videos and istall large applications from the <em>Google Play Store.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>To crown it, you also get the ability to expand the storage to a maximum of 128GB using an external memory card.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With the F3, you can run multiple applications at the same time since you get 4GB of RAM. With this amount, you can have several apps running in the background and have no performance issues. No lags, no overheating and no app crashes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="OPPO F3 Selfie Camera Specifications" class="alignnone size-full td-animation-stack-type1-2 wp-image-2221" src="https://kenyaprice.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/oppo-f3_149396281180.jpg" style="height:375px; width:600px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><u>OPPO F3 CAMERA</u></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Primary camera: 13 MP Camera</li>\r\n	<li>Front Camera: 16 MP + 8 MP Dual Front Camera</li>\r\n	<li>Video Recording: 2160p@30fps, 1080p@30fps</li>\r\n	<li>Camera Features: Geo Tagging, HDR</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The OPPO F3 throws some heavy punches in the camera department. Let&rsquo;s start off with the selfie one. In the front facing camera is a dual lens. One is 16MP while the other is 8MP (both are in the front). Therefore, you can switch from a wide angle lens when taking a group selfie or the normal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Speaking of the rear facing camera, you get 13MP. All these cameras also have features to help you take better pictures. These include autofocus, face detection touch to focus and HDR.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><u>MULTIMEDIA</u></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Audio Player: MP3, WAV, eAAC+, FLAC</li>\r\n	<li>Video Player: MP4, DivX, XviD, WMV, H.264, H.263</li>\r\n	<li>Games: Yes</li>\r\n	<li>FM Radio: No</li>\r\n	<li>Speakers: Yes</li>\r\n	<li>Audio Jack: 3.5mm Audio Jack</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="OPPO F3 Battery Specs" class="alignnone size-full td-animation-stack-type1-2 wp-image-2222" src="https://kenyaprice.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/oppo-f3_149396281140.jpg" style="height:375px; width:600px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><u>OPPO F3 BATTERY</u></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Type: Non-removable Li-Ion 3200 mAh battery</li>\r\n	<li>Stand by: NA</li>\r\n	<li>Talk time: NA</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>OPPO F3 is powered by a 3200mAh battery. This large capacity will definitely last the whole day under normal usage.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><u>CONNECTIVITY</u></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>GPRS: Yes</li>\r\n	<li>Edge: Yes</li>\r\n	<li>WLAN: Wi-Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n/ac, dual-band, WiFi Direct, hotspot</li>\r\n	<li>Bluetooth: v4.1, A2DP, LE</li>\r\n	<li>USB: microUSB v2.0</li>\r\n	<li>GPS Facility: with A-GPS</li>\r\n	<li>Browser: HTML5</li>\r\n	<li>3G Speed: HSPA 42.2/5.76 Mbps, LTE-A (2CA) Cat6 300/50 Mbps</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="Oppo phones at Jumia" class="alignnone size-full td-animation-stack-type1-2 wp-image-2227" src="https://kenyaprice.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/oppo-f3_149396281160.jpg" style="height:375px; width:600px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><u>NETWORK SUPPORT</u></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>3G: HSDPA 850 / 900 / 1900 / 2100 MHz</li>\r\n	<li>2G: GSM 850 / 900 / 1800 / 1900 MHz</li>\r\n	<li>4G: LTE</li>\r\n	<li>With the 4G LTE support, you can stream videos and brose faster in the F3.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong><u>OTHER FEATURES</u></strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Sensors Fingerprint Sensor</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="Buy the OPPO F3 in Kenya Jumia" class="alignnone size-full td-animation-stack-type1-2 wp-image-2228" src="https://kenyaprice.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/oppo-f3_149396281190.jpg" style="height:400px; width:640px" /></p>\r\n', '', '', 'JCG1313', NULL, '', NULL, 'visible', 34598, 32950, 1, 'oppo-f3-13mp-camera-64gb-4gb-ram-dual-sim-5-5-inch-gold.jpg', 'oppo-f3-13mp-camera-64gb-4gb-ram-dual-sim-5-5-inch-gold-2.jpg', 'oppo-f3-13mp-camera-64gb-4gb-ram-dual-sim-5-5-inch-gold-3.jpg', 'oppo-f3-13mp-camera-64gb-4gb-ram-dual-sim-5-5-inch-gold-4.jpg', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'oppo-f3-13mp-camera-64gb-4gb-ram-dual-sim-5-5-inch-gold', '2017-09-21 20:49:11', '2017-09-21 20:49:11'),
