(517, 1, 21, 61, 1, 29, NULL, 'Huawei Y3C, 4GB, 512MB RAM, 5MP Camera, Dual SIM Color- Black', '<h2><strong>Key Features</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>10.2 CM (4&rdquo;) Screen</li>\r\n	<li>5MP Main Camera &amp; 2MP Front camera with Dual LED Flash</li>\r\n	<li>1730 mAh Battery</li>\r\n	<li>Android 4.4 + HUAWEI EMUI 3.0 Lite</li>\r\n	<li>Dual SIM (3G and GSM)</li>\r\n	<li>512 RAM + 4GB ROM + 32 GB External</li>\r\n	<li>Special Screen technology for Lowest Power Consumption &amp; Low heating</li>\r\n	<li>Gesture Control : Double tap to awaken screen</li>\r\n	<li>Power Saving Mode</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<h2><strong>Product Specifications</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Display &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Type:IPS LCD capacitive touchscreen, 16M colors</li>\r\n	<li>Size:4.0 inches (~56.4% screen-to-body ratio)</li>\r\n	<li>Resolution:480 x 854 pixels (~245 ppi pixel density)</li>\r\n	<li>Multitouch &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Platform &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>OS:Android 4.4.4 (KitKat)</li>\r\n	<li>Chipset:Mediatek MT6582</li>\r\n	<li>CPU:Quad-core 1.2 GHz Cortex-A7</li>\r\n	<li>GPU:Mali-400MP2</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Storage</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Internal:4 GB</li>\r\n	<li>512 MB RAM</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Camera &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Primary:5 MP, dual-LED flash</li>\r\n	<li>Video:720p</li>\r\n	<li>Secondary:2 MP</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Comms &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>WLAN:Wi-Fi 802.11 b/g/n, Wi-Fi Direct, hotspot</li>\r\n	<li>Bluetooth:4.0, A2DP</li>\r\n	<li>GPS:Yes, with A-GPS</li>\r\n	<li>FM radio</li>\r\n	<li>microUSB 2.0</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Features &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Sensors:Accelerometer</li>\r\n	<li>Messaging:SMS(threaded view), MMS, Email, Push Email, IM</li>\r\n	<li>Browser:HTML</li>\r\n	<li>MP3/WAV/eAAC+ player</li>\r\n	<li>MP4/H.264 player</li>\r\n	<li>Photo/video editor</li>\r\n	<li>Document viewer</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Battery&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Removable Li-Po 1730 mAh battery</li>\r\n	<li>Stand-by:Up to 280 h (2G) / Up to 220 h (3G)</li>\r\n	<li>Talk time:Up to 6 h 40 min (2G) / Up to 7 h 30 min (3G)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<h1 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Huawei Y3C (Dual SIM)</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Huawei Y3C Dual SIM<strong>&nbsp;</strong>smartphone is an excellent choice for those seeking a balance between functionality and powerful performance. The 4inch IPS LCD capacitive touchscreen casts sharp images, animations, videos, and other onscreen elements at a screen resolution of 480 x 854 pixels.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/HU687EL0UR5K8NAFAMZ/9109bd332683b991466030688a3cb031.jpg" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/HU687EL0UR5K8NAFAMZ/9109bd332683b991466030688a3cb031.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>4GB Internal Storage Space</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The Huawei Y3C Dual Sim specs incorporate some great features, including the 4GB internal storage. This storage system can be expanded up to 32GB via a microSD card. You have all the space to store data like pictures, videos, music, and other such files, for easy access when you need them.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="Huawei Y3C Dual Sim" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/HU687EL0UR5K8NAFAMZ/6eecbe076ef463e72fa20588a82b8fd5.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>With KitKat on Top</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The Huawei Y3C Dual Sim reviews fortify the smartphone&rsquo;s shining performance and credibility. It is installed with the advanced Android v4.4.4 KitKat operating system that makes using this smartphone easy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="Huawei Y3C Dual Sim" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/HU687EL0UR5K8NAFAMZ/bfb785471e98b5da78c04e2a013e3b3e.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Surprisingly Powerful</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The Huawei Y3C is powered by the Mediatek MT6582 chipset that houses a Quad Core 1.2GHz Cortex A7 processor, which efficiently handles all your operations. The Mali 400MP2 graphics processor handles graphics intensive tasks efficiently, along with heavy processes and applications. Switching between apps takes minimal time and effort on this phone, thanks to a 512MB RAM module.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="Huawei Y3C Dual Sim" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/HU687EL0UR5K8NAFAMZ/e5338c1c824a6c50d610c64f8cec1700.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Long Lasting Charge</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The Huawei Y3C battery, which has an amazing capacity of 1730mAh, powers this smartphone. This battery ensures your phone runs for longer periods of time, giving you more time on the move. This battery offers a talk time of up to 6 hours and 40 minutes on the 2G network and up to 7 hours and 30 minutes on the 3G network.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="Huawei Y3C Dual Sim" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/HU687EL0UR5K8NAFAMZ/385d115a6bb5d08f52abdfed44adaa66.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle" /></p>\r\n', '', '', 'GLN1231', NULL, '', NULL, 'visible', 3900, 3679, 1, 'huawei-y3c-4gb-512mb-ram-5mp-camera-dual-sim-color-black.jpg', 'huawei-y3c-4gb-512mb-ram-5mp-camera-dual-sim-color-black-2.jpg', 'huawei-y3c-4gb-512mb-ram-5mp-camera-dual-sim-color-black-3.jpg', 'huawei-y3c-4gb-512mb-ram-5mp-camera-dual-sim-color-black-4.jpg', 'huawei-y3c-4gb-512mb-ram-5mp-camera-dual-sim-color-black-5.jpg', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'huawei-y3c-4gb-512mb-ram-5mp-camera-dual-sim-color-black', '2017-09-23 13:41:44', '2017-09-23 13:41:44'),
(518, 1, 21, 61, 2, 28, NULL, 'INFINIX Zero 4 Model X555 (16MP, 32GB, 3GB RAM,Dual SIM) Grey ', '<div class="title" style="box-sizing: border-box; line-height: 17px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; font-family: Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;"><strong>Key Features</strong></div>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Display Size:5.5 Inch Screen</li>\r\n	<li>Display Type:Full HD Touchscreen</li>\r\n	<li>Internal Memory:32GBM 3GB RAM</li>\r\n	<li>OS:Android M</li>\r\n	<li>Primary Camera16MP&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Secondary : 8MP</li>\r\n	<li>Number Of SIM&nbsp; : Dual SIM</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<h3><strong>Design &amp; Display</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Design: Frame metal and plastic black cover.</li>\r\n	<li>Dimension:&nbsp;153.2 X 76.4 X 7.8 mm.</li>\r\n	<li>Screen size: 5.5 inch.</li>\r\n	<li>Screen Resolution: 1080 x 1920 FHD.</li>\r\n	<li>Screen Density: 440 ppi.</li>\r\n	<li>Screen Protection: Corning Gorilla Glass 4.</li>\r\n	<li>Screen Type: IPS LCD capacitive touchscreen, 16M colors.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Network.</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>GSM: GSM 850/900/1800/1900.</li>\r\n	<li>3G:HSDPA 850 / 900 / 2100.</li>\r\n	<li>4G:FDD-LTE 3(1800) / 7(2600) / 20(800) .</li>\r\n	<li>SIM Type: Dual Nano SIM.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Operating System</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Android version: Infinix XOS based on Android 6.0.1 Marshmallow.</li>\r\n	<li>Processor Speed: Dual-core 2.3 GHz Cortex-A72 + quad-core 2.3 GHz Cortex-A53 + quad-core 1.4 GHz Cortex-A53.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Processor Type: 64 bit MediaTek Helio X20 chipset.</li>\r\n	<li>Graphics Processor: Mali T720.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Camera</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Main Camera: 16MP rear camera with dual LED flash, OIS , 4X Sharper Zoom and f/2.0 lens , and Laser Focus.</li>\r\n	<li>Video Recording: 4K (ultra-HD).</li>\r\n	<li>Front Camera: 8MP with led flash.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Memory</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>RAM: 3GB.</li>\r\n	<li>Internal Storage Memory: 32GB.</li>\r\n	<li>SD card Slot: Yes, up to 128GB.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Battery</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Size: 3200 mAh.</li>\r\n	<li>Property: Fast Charging or Infinix Xcharge 3A PE + 2.0, Non-Removable.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Sensors</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Fingerprint Scanner, Accelerometer, Proximity.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Connectivity</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Bluetooth: v4.1.</li>\r\n	<li>USB: microUSB v2.0, USB OTG.</li>\r\n	<li>GPS: A-GPS.</li>\r\n	<li>Wi-Fi: WI Fi 802.11 a/b/g/n, Wi-Fi direct, hotspot.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p>Infinix is at it again with the POWERFUL&nbsp;<strong>Infinix Zero 4 X555</strong>&nbsp;a 4G LTE phone with a 5.5&prime; with a Full HD Screen, Octacore Processor, a 16MP rear back camera and 8MP front camera for awesome selfies. What&#39;s more, this awesome phone runs on Android M and has an awesome 3200mAh battery capacity.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="image" src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/DRortGBjj7IzmafQdONp52z2UKVBof2THTrSd0qVxbAm_Zt3znuTp-XadIJ3xTXnIIgKIaBbaHKGLp8yNplM8ih_LzxHPQPUmKEMoj1e-zHKpw2dpPMYk7fX_G0rAjwGuLbXxV3w" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:326px; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle; width:660px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="image" src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/RYC491pKq4Z9n7uMvzmHLfuXroB-8PmA9_Nd_a-Nh4P86I1GA322PklbzBqTqfNmww_eKl1jUB1DE_Ab0U4PJ5aFO8goSRlRLyttnAxxc8ekTN8LX02V1n-oOp91M0kJGR_OCVlI" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:437px; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle; width:655px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="image" src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/w_591swS0-4AonpyNdUGo0qHZ6p5NzTJOphKJM4cRhdcosDqozHTnQ3qa1VRAnvBasfAGbp44lF51j7tUHVe9hnvqRVeS08vWuVEV3xEZzycGWXOBhM6ce6FWDWNBpsnzRe5j8eZ" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:156px; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-