e together to offer top-notch performance in basic and heavy duty tasks. Data storage is not a problem at all,&nbsp;as there is 32GB of internal storage on-board, which can be further expanded up to 128GB via microSD card. The handset offers impressive 5.1 surround sound through dual front speakers that feature HTC&#39;s signature BoomSound technology.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Take Best Pictures</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>In the imaging department, the smartphone sports a 20-megapixel camera sensor. The camera has a dual-LED flash and it is capable of recording Full HD videos. The phone has a 4-megapixel front camera with UltraPixel technology, which takes breathtaking selfies even in low-light conditions. Other features include simultaneous video and image recording, face and smile detection, HDR, panorama and much more.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="image" src="http://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/HT791ELAB5I9NAFAMZ/1bbadc6d2985b9d3279f6631e318c9ab_938123dd61183336011f88be05f2f79b3464683e.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:308px; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle; width:554px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<h2>Android Powered</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The phone runs Android 5.0.2 Lollipop with HTC&#39;s Sense 7 UI on top. Android Lollipop is one of the most advanced mobile operating systems out there, offering a variety of functions in addition to official access to all of Google&#39;s popular web services. Sense 7 brings its own set of value-added features, such as BlinkFeed and HTC Zoe, along with a fast and smooth user experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', '', 'JCG1374', NULL, '', NULL, 'visible', 31500, 30000, 1, 'htc-one-m9-plus-20-7mp-camera-3gb-ram-32gb-silver.jpg', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'htc-one-m9-plus-20-7mp-camera-3gb-ram-32gb-silver', '2017-09-28 08:24:53', '2017-09-28 08:24:53'),
(592, 1, 21, 61, 2, 31, NULL, 'HTC Model One (M8)  (32GB, 2GB RAM) Grey', '<p><strong>Key features</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="color:rgb(17, 17, 17)">3G/4G LTE connectivity</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="color:rgb(17, 17, 17)">Android 4.4.2 (KitKat) with HTC Sense</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="color:rgb(17, 17, 17)">2.3GHz Qualcomm Snapdragon 800 quad-core</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="color:rgb(17, 17, 17)">5.0-inch Full HD 1080p with 440ppi display</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="color:rgb(17, 17, 17)">Dual camera with UltraPixel</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="color:rgb(17, 17, 17)">Front 5-MP camera with 1080p video</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="color:rgb(17, 17, 17)">32 GB storage + 2 GB of RAM</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="color:rgb(17, 17, 17)"><span style="color:rgb(17, 17, 17)">Wireless-N Wi-Fi + Bluetooth 4.0 + NFC, 2600 mAh battery capacity</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p>DISPLAY</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Type Super LCD3 capacitive touchscreen, 16M colors</li>\r\n	<li>Size 5.0 inches (~66.7% screen-to-body ratio)</li>\r\n	<li>Resolution 1080 x 1920 pixels (~441 ppi pixel density)</li>\r\n	<li>Multitouch Yes</li>\r\n	<li>Protection Corning Gorilla Glass 3</li>\r\n	<li>- HTC Sense UI 6.0</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>PLATFORM OS</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Android OS, v4.4.2 (KitKat), upgradable to v5.0 (Lollipop)</li>\r\n	<li>Chipset Qualcomm MSM8974AB Snapdragon 801</li>\r\n	<li>CPU Quad-core 2.3 GHz (US/EMEA)/ 2.5 GHz (Asia, China) Krait 400</li>\r\n	<li>GPU Adreno 330</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>MEMORY</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Card slot microSD, up to 128 GB</li>\r\n	<li>Internal 32 GB, 2 GB RAM</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>CAMERA</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Primary Dual 4 MP, 2688?1520 pixels, autofocus, dual-LED (dual tone) flash, check quality</li>\r\n	<li>Features 1/3&#39;&#39; sensor size, 2&micro;m pixel size, automatic simultaneous video and image recording, geo-tagging, face/smile detection, HDR, panorama</li>\r\n	<li>Video 1080p@60fps, 720p@120fps, HDR, stereo sound rec., check quality</li>\r\n	<li>Secondary 5 MP, 1080p@30fps, HDR</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>SOUND</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Alert types Vibration; MP3, WAV ringtones</li>\r\n	<li>Loudspeaker Yes, with stereo speakers</li>\r\n	<li>3.5mm jack Yes</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>BATTERY</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Non-removable Li-Po 2600 mAh battery</li>\r\n	<li>Stand-by Up to 271 h (2G) / Up to 496 h (3G)</li>\r\n	<li>Talk time Up to 14 h (2G) / Up to 20 h (3G)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p>Introducing one of the most anticipated phones for the year 2014, the HTC One (M8) is finally here. HTC&#39;s answer to the big boys and it sure is impressive. As beautiful to look at as it is to hold, this beauty comes in a premium all metal uni-body, a large 5&quot; dazzling display and the curiosity sparking duo camera at the back. And of course packs pure performance.<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="Image result for htc logo" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/HT791EL1NCWE8NAFAMZ/c397ed2b6746850406ea73834ae4bec2.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:200px; margin:46px auto 30px; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle; width:200px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Sheer Beauty</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The all metal aluminium body with sleek lines and soft curves has been crafted to fit perfectly in the palm of your hand. It curves around the screen with no edges or seams to make it one of the most comfortable phones to hold. Combine innovative smartphone design and superior craftsmanship and what you get is the new One M8.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/HT791EL1NCWE8NAFAMZ/217f894b17470e9fc5b5bd2d99742329.jpg" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/HT791EL1NCWE8NAFAMZ/217f894b17470e9fc5b5bd2d99742329.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Large Screen&nbsp; Display</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The 5.0&quot; screen on the device is bright and sharp enough to make anyone enjoy this phone. This is courtesy of the high resolution LCD3 display. View, watch and browse content on this large screen comfortably.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<img alt="image" src="https://ss7.vzw.com/is/image/VerizonWireless/premium-design-looks-feels-good?$device-pdp-primary$" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Duo Camera</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The M8 sports a one of a kind new revolutionary camera that uses a dual camera mode to take amazing photos. The duo camera delivers intuitive focusing features, you have the option of choosing where to focus, even after the shot has been taken. The main Ultrapixel 4MP camera takes the photo while the lens equipped with a 2MP unit, measures the depth of subject for more detailed shots. It also has a much reduced autofocus time of 300ms meaning quicker and blur-free snaps.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="image" src="https://ss7.vzw.com/is/image/VerizonWireless/snap-great-photos?$device-pdp-primary$" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:371px; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle; width:535px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Stay Updated</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Immerse your mind with content from HTC BlinkFeed on your Home screen. Get updates from your favorite sources including news, entertainment, sports, fashion, social networks, weather and more. A simplified menu and continual scrolling make the experience easy and fluid.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="image" src="https://ss7.vzw.com/is/image/VerizonWireless/blink-feed?$device-pdp-vertical$" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>More Louder</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Music, videos and games sound powerful with dual front-facing speakers and HTC BoomSound&trade;. An enhanced amplifier offers balance to boost bass and deliver clear vocals. The new speakers make new HTC One (M8) 25 percent louder than its predecessor.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="image" src="https://ss7.vzw.com/is/image/VerizonWireless/hear-clear-balanced-sound?$device-pdp-vertical$" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Improved Battery</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Get up to 40% improvement on the battery life of the HTC One (M8) when comparing it to its predecessor. In addition to that, the handset comes with battery saving modes that limit the use of resources when the HTC One (M8) is on standby for reduced battery consumption. Not only that, the HTC One (M8) comes with an Extreme Power Save Mode that gives you up to 2 weeks of standby time. The HTC One (M8) will always keep up with you and your busy mobile life.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="image" src="https://ss7.vzw.com/is/image/VerizonWireless/enhanced-power-storage?$device-pdp-primary$" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:417px; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle; width:601px" /></p>\r\n', '', '', 'JCG1375', NULL, '', NULL, 'visible', 24569, 23399, 1, 'htc-model-one-m8-32gb-2gb-ram-grey.jpg', 'htc-model-one-m8-32gb-2gb-ram-grey-2.jpg', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'htc-model-one-m8-32gb-2gb-ram-grey', '2017-09-28 09:13:16', '2017-09-28 09:13:16'),
(593, 1, 21, 61, 2, 31, NULL, ' HTC Desire 10 Pro ( 20MP Camera , 64GB, 4GB RAM)white', '<p><strong>Key Features</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>OS: Android OS, v6.0 (Marshmallow)</li>\r\n	<li>Size: &nbsp;5.5 inches (~70.5% screen-to-body ratio)</li>\r\n	<li>Internal: 64 GB, 4 GB RAM</li>\r\n	<li><span style="color:rgb(96, 96, 96); font-family:roboto,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size:12px">Primary: 20 MP</span></li>\r\n	<li><span style="color:rgb(96, 96, 96); font-family:roboto,helvetica,arial,sans-serif; font-size:12px">Secondary: 13 MP</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p><strong>Key Features</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>SIM:Single SIM (Nano-SIM)</li>\r\n	<li>Type:Super LCD5 capacitive touchscreen, 16M colors</li>\r\n	<li>Size:5.2 inches (~71.1% screen-to-body ratio)</li>\r\n	<li>Resolution:1440 x 2560 pixels (~565 ppi pixel density)</li>\r\n	<li>Multitouch:Yes</li>\r\n	<li>OS:Android OS, v6.0.1 (Marshmallow)</li>\r\n	<li>Chipset:Qualcomm MSM8996 Snapdragon 820</li>\r\n	<li>CPU:Dual-core 2.15 GHz Kryo &amp; dual-core 1.6 GHz Kryo</li>\r\n	<li>GPU:Adreno 530</li>\r\n	<li>Card slot:microSD, up to 200 GB (dedicated slot)</li>\r\n	<li>Internal:32 GB, 4 GB RAM</li>\r\n	<li>Primary:12 MP, f/1.8, 26mm, OIS, laser autofocus, dual-LED (dual tone) flash</li>\r\n	<li>Video:2160p@30fps, 1080p@60fps, 720p@120fps, HDR, stereo sound rec.</li>\r\n	<li>Secondary:5 MP, f/1.8, 23mm, OIS, autofocus, 1.34 &micro;m pixel size, 1080p, HDR</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<p>HTC Desire 10 Pro smartphone comes with a 5.50-inch touchscreen display with a resolution of 1080 pixels by 1920 pixels at a PPI of 400 pixels per inch.&nbsp;The HTC Desire 10 Pro is powered by 1.8GHz octa-core MediaTek Helio P10 processor and it comes with 3GB of RAM. The phone packs 32GB of internal storage. HTC Desire 10 Pro packs a 20-megapixel primary camera on the rear and a 13-megapixel front shooter for selfies.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="image" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/HT791EL0TPMBSNAFAMZ/e13489bffc72dbf98f7f0255c0a5d2d5.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:210px; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle; width:300px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Capture Clear Photos</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Take stunning photos using a 20MP camera</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="image" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/HT791EL0TPMBSNAFAMZ/d1b50dfa700b5e78302285613b629dbf.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>13MP Selfie Camera</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Smile for the selfie camera that has the same sensor pixel count as the main camera in many other phones. If you&rsquo;re serious about great-looking selfies then you&rsquo;ll appreciate the HTC Desire 10 pro&rsquo;s 13MP selfie camera. It promises you higher resolution selfies that capture more scenery and good time with friends. This selfie camera also features a built-in screen flash, which helps you take brighter selfies in low light.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="image" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/HT791EL0TPMBSNAFAMZ/9f01bf13f3a6de9b9c344f2d2d823987.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Fingerprint Security</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Protect your valuable data. HTC Desire 10 pro&rsquo;s fingerprint security keeps your data safe, but quickly unlocks at just the touch of your finger. The sensor recognizes your fingerprint from almost every angle and position. And, with the App Lock function in Boost+, your fingerprint can also be used to help prevent your apps from being opened by others.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="image" src="https://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/HT791EL0TPMBSNAFAMZ/bf3dcfa0a3be364b7ec26fabf0a81f3a.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>More Storage Space</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>HTC Desire 10 pro gives you more space for the things that are important with a massive 4GB of RAM and 64GB storage space. So you can load up on photos, videos, movies, games and more. And if that&rsquo;s not enough room, HTC Desire 10 pro has SD card support for up to 2TB expandable memory.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Fully Customizable</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Make your phone as unique as you are. HTC Freestyle Layout frees you from an onscreen grid and lets you get creative. Drag icons, stickers and widgets anywhere. Layer them, overlap them, group them and more. You can even link stickers to apps, and get rid of onscreen icons entirely. The home screen is yours, use it your way.</p>\r\n', '', '', 'JCG1376', NULL, '', NULL, 'visible', 27719, 26399, 1, 'htc-desire-10-pro-64gb-4gb-ram-20mp-camera-mint-green-64gb-4gb-ram-mint-green.jpg', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'htc-desire-10-pro-20mp-camera-64gb-4gb-ram-white', '2017-09-28 09:46:56', '2017-09-28 09:46:56'),
