ma-nova,sans-serif; font-size:12.6px">CAMERA</span></strong><br />\r\n<span style="color:rgb(37, 39, 42); font-family:proxima-nova-n9,proxima-nova,sans-serif; font-size:12.6px">Primary 20 MP, f/2.2, 28mm, autofocus, dual-LED (dual tone) flash, check quality</span><br />\r\n<span style="color:rgb(37, 39, 42); font-family:proxima-nova-n9,proxima-nova,sans-serif; font-size:12.6px">Features 1/2.4&quot; sensor size, 1.2 &micro;m pixel size, geo-tagging, touch focus, face/smile detection, HDR, panorama</span><br />\r\n<span style="color:rgb(37, 39, 42); font-family:proxima-nova-n9,proxima-nova,sans-serif; font-size:12.6px">Video 2160p@30fps, 1080p@60fps, 720p@120fps, HDR, stereo sound rec., check quality</span><br />\r\n<span style="color:rgb(37, 39, 42); font-family:proxima-nova-n9,proxima-nova,sans-serif; font-size:12.6px">Secondary 4 MP, f/2.0, 27mm, 1/3&quot; sensor size, 2&micro;m pixel size, 1080p@30fps, HDR</span><br />\r\n<strong><span style="color:rgb(37, 39, 42); font-family:proxima-nova-n9,proxima-nova,sans-serif; font-size:12.6px">SOUND</span></strong><br />\r\n<span style="color:rgb(37, 39, 42); font-family:proxima-nova-n9,proxima-nova,sans-serif; font-size:12.6px">Alert types Vibration; MP3, WAV ringtones</span><br />\r\n<span style="color:rgb(37, 39, 42); font-family:proxima-nova-n9,proxima-nova,sans-serif; font-size:12.6px">Loudspeaker Yes, with stereo speakers</span><br />\r\n<span style="color:rgb(37, 39, 42); font-family:proxima-nova-n9,proxima-nova,sans-serif; font-size:12.6px">3.5mm jack Yes</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong><span style="color:rgb(37, 39, 42); font-family:proxima-nova-n9,proxima-nova,sans-serif; font-size:12.6px">BATTERY</span></strong><br />\r\n<span style="color:rgb(37, 39, 42); font-family:proxima-nova-n9,proxima-nova,sans-serif; font-size:12.6px">Non-removable Li-Po 2840 mAh battery</span></p>\r\n', '<p><strong>HTC One M9</strong>&nbsp;is an Android&nbsp;5.0.2 Lollipop based&nbsp;smartphone, which comes with 3GB of RAM,&nbsp;Cat 6 LTE connectivity and a 2 GHz quad-core Snapdragon 810 processor for effortless multitasking.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Best Design</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The smartphone features a 5-inch&nbsp;sapphire glass Full HD display with (1920x1080 pixels)&nbsp;screen resolution having a pixel density of 335 PPI. The screen also has a coating of Corning&rsquo;s Gorilla Glass 4 for advanced resistance against scratches and everyday wear and tear. The smartphone also sports a metal body with gold and silver finish which reflects a premium feel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="image" src="http://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/HT791ELAB5I9NAFAMZ/1bbadc6d2985b9d3279f6631e318c9ab_bdd53a1cb1780adfe88cdd42fcb1ec8c933dd479.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:354px; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle; width:395px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<h2>Powerful Processor</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The device is powered by a 2 GHz quad-core Snapdragon 810 processor paired with 3GB of RAM and Adreno 430 graphics, which combine together to offer top-notch performance in basic and heavy duty tasks. Data storage is not a problem at all,&nbsp;as there is 32GB of internal storage on-board, which can be further expanded up to 128GB via microSD card. The handset offers impressive 5.1 surround sound through dual front speakers that feature HTC&#39;s signature BoomSound technology.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Take Best Pictures</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>In the imaging department, the smartphone sports a 20-megapixel camera sensor. The camera has a dual-LED flash and it is capable of recording Full HD videos. The phone has a 4-megapixel front camera with UltraPixel technology, which takes breathtaking selfies even in low-light conditions. Other features include simultaneous video and image recording, face and smile detection, HDR, panorama and much more.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt="image" src="http://static.jumia.co.ke/cms/external/pet/HT791ELAB5I9NAFAMZ/1bbadc6d2985b9d3279f6631e318c9ab_938123dd61183336011f88be05f2f79b3464683e.jpg" style="border:0px; box-sizing:border-box; display:block; height:308px; margin:30px auto; max-width:710px; vertical-align:middle; width:554px" /></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<h2>Android Powered</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The phone runs Android 5.0.2 Lollipop with HTC&#39;s Sense 7 UI on top. Android Lollipop is one of the most advanced mobile operating systems out there, offering a variety of functions in addition to official access to all of Google&#39;s popular web services. Sense 7 brings its own set of value-added features, such as BlinkFeed and HTC Zoe, along with a fast and smooth user experience.</p>\r\n', '', '', 'JCG1377', NULL, '', NULL, 'visible', 29399, 27999, 1, 'htc-one-m9-20-7mp-camera-3gb-ram-32gb-grey.jpg', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'htc-one-m9-20-7mp-camera-3gb-ram-32gb-grey', '2017-09-28 09:59:23', '2017-09-28 09:59:23'),
